## 📋 PROJECT-SPECIFIC RULES

### AInfluencer Platform Context
- **Core Goal**: Ultra-realistic AI content generation (images + videos)
- **Key Feature**: Face consistency across all generations
- **Unique Value**: Self-hosted, free, fully automated
- **Target Users**: Content creators, influencers, developers

### Critical Features to Always Improve
1. **Image Generation Quality**: Realism, face consistency, artifact reduction
2. **Video Generation Quality**: Motion smoothness, temporal consistency
3. **Face Consistency**: IP-Adapter, InstantID, multiple face references
4. **Anti-Detection**: Metadata removal, quality variation, humanization
5. **Automation**: Batch processing, scheduled generation, workflow templates
6. **User Interface**: Intuitive, fast, beautiful, responsive
7. **Performance**: Generation speed, UI responsiveness, resource usage

### Technology-Specific Guidelines

#### Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- Use Server Components by default
- Client Components only when needed (interactivity, state, hooks)
- Use `next/image` for all images
- Implement proper loading.tsx and error.tsx
- Use route handlers for API endpoints
- Optimize bundle size (code splitting, dynamic imports)
- Use proper metadata API for SEO

#### TypeScript
- Strict mode always
- No `any` types (use `unknown` if needed)
- Proper interfaces for all data structures
- Generic types for reusable components
- Discriminated unions for complex state
- Type guards for runtime validation

#### React
- Functional components only
- Hooks for state and side effects
- Memoization when appropriate (useMemo, useCallback)
- Proper key props for lists
- Error boundaries for error handling
- Accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)

#### Python/FastAPI
- Type hints everywhere
- Pydantic models for validation
- Async/await for I/O operations
- Proper error handling and logging
- Comprehensive docstrings
- Environment variable management

#### ComfyUI Integration
- Proper error handling for API calls
- WebSocket for real-time updates
- Queue management for batch operations
- Progress tracking and reporting
- Workflow validation before execution
- Resource management (GPU memory)

---

## 🎨 UI/UX GUIDELINES

### Design Principles
- **Modern**: Clean, contemporary design language
- **Intuitive**: Self-explanatory, minimal learning curve
- **Fast**: Instant feedback, smooth animations
- **Responsive**: Works on all screen sizes
- **Accessible**: WCAG AA compliance
- **Consistent**: Unified design system

### Component Standards
- Use shadcn/ui components when possible
- Consistent spacing (Tailwind spacing scale)
- Consistent colors (theme-aware)
- Consistent typography (font sizes, weights)
- Consistent animations (duration, easing)
- Loading states for all async operations
- Error states with helpful messages
- Empty states with clear CTAs

### User Flows
- Minimize steps to complete tasks
- Provide clear progress indicators
- Allow undo/redo where possible
- Save work automatically
- Provide helpful tooltips and hints
- Show examples and templates

---

## 🔒 SECURITY & PRIVACY

### Security Requirements
- **Input Validation**: Validate and sanitize all user inputs
- **Authentication**: Secure auth if needed (JWT, sessions)
- **Authorization**: Proper permission checks
- **Data Protection**: Encrypt sensitive data
- **API Security**: Rate limiting, CORS, CSRF protection
- **Dependencies**: Keep dependencies updated, audit regularly

### Privacy Requirements
- **Local Processing**: All AI processing happens locally
- **No Telemetry**: No tracking without explicit consent
- **Data Minimization**: Only collect necessary data
- **User Control**: Users control their data
- **Transparency**: Clear privacy policy

---

## 📊 MONITORING & OBSERVABILITY

### What to Monitor
- **Performance**: Response times, generation times, UI metrics
- **Errors**: Error rates, error types, stack traces
- **Usage**: Feature usage, user flows, drop-off points
- **Resources**: CPU, GPU, memory, disk usage
- **Quality**: Generation quality scores, user ratings

### Logging Standards
- Structured logging (JSON format)
- Appropriate log levels (DEBUG, INFO, WARN, ERROR)
- Include context (user ID, request ID, timestamps)
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, personal info)
- Log errors with full stack traces
- Log performance metrics

---

## 🧪 TESTING REQUIREMENTS

### Test Coverage
- **Unit Tests**: All business logic, utilities, helpers
- **Integration Tests**: API endpoints, database operations
- **E2E Tests**: Critical user flows
- **Visual Tests**: UI components, layouts
- **Performance Tests**: Load testing, stress testing

### Testing Best Practices
- Write tests before fixing bugs (TDD when possible)
- Test edge cases and error conditions
- Use mocks for external dependencies
- Keep tests fast and independent
- Use descriptive test names
- Maintain test data fixtures

---

## 📚 DOCUMENTATION STANDARDS

### Code Documentation
- **Docstrings**: All public functions, classes, modules
- **Comments**: Explain "why", not "what"
- **Type Hints**: Self-documenting code with types
- **README**: Keep updated with setup and usage

### User Documentation
- **Setup Guides**: Clear, step-by-step instructions
- **Feature Guides**: How to use each feature
- **Troubleshooting**: Common issues and solutions
- **API Documentation**: OpenAPI/Swagger for APIs

---

## 🚀 DEPLOYMENT & DEVOPS

### Deployment Principles
- **Automation**: Automated builds, tests, deployments
- **Versioning**: Semantic versioning (SemVer)
- **Rollback**: Ability to rollback quickly
- **Monitoring**: Health checks, alerts
- **Backup**: Regular backups of data

### Environment Management
- **Development**: Local development environment
- **Staging**: Pre-production testing
- **Production**: Production environment
- **Secrets**: Environment variables, secure storage
- **Configuration**: Environment-specific configs

